'''Investment arbitration''' is [[arbitration]] in [[investment]] [[dispute resolution|disputes]] between foreign investors and the host state which finds place within the framework of a either a [[bilateral investment treaty]] (BIT) between the host state and the investor's state or a [[multilateral treaty]], such as the [[NAFTA]] or the [[Energy Charter Treaty]].

