'''Roberto Ramón''' "'''Chato'''" '''Alemán Zubieta''' (1921 – 18 July 2009) was a Panamanian lawyer, diplomat, politician and businessman. He served as Ambassador of [[Panama]] to the United States from 1968 to 1969.<ref name=ripon>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ripon.edu/2013/09/02/alumni-profile-jose-miguel-aleman-78-changes-panama-through-political-activity/|title=Alumni Profile: José Miguel Alemán ’78 changes Panama through political activity|website=ripon.edu|date=2 September 2013|accessdate=2 August 2018}}</ref><ref name=panamaamerica>{{Cite web|url=https://www.panamaamerica.com.pa/nacion/roberto-chato-aleman-fallecio-ayer-en-la-capital-448141|title=Roberto “Chato” Alemán falleció ayer en la capital|work=Panamá América|date=19 July 2009|accessdate=2 August 2018|language=es}}</ref> In 1951, he married María Teresa Healy Quelquejue (born 1928), who was a descendant of the wealthy de Roux family.<ref name=geocities>{{Cite web|url=http://www.geocities.ws/derouxblondel/d5.html#c64|title=Familia de Roux|publisher=GEOCITIES.ws|accessdate=2 August 2018}}</ref> Together they had six children, including the diplomat [[Jaime Aleman Healy|Jaime Eduardo]] (born 1953) and politician [[José Miguel Alemán|José Miguel]] (born 1958).<ref name=ripon/><ref name=geocities/>
