{{ infobox |title = World Strategic Forum | abovestyle = | above = |imagestyle = |captionstyle = | image = [[File:Logo_of_the_World_Strategic_Forum.png]] | caption = | headerstyle = | header1 = | label1 = Organized by | data1 = [[International Economic Forum of the Americas]] | header2 = | label2 = Type | data2 = International Conference | header3 = | label3 = Frequency | data3 = Annually | header4 = | label4 = Founded | data4 = 2011 | header5 = | label5 = Founded by | data5 = [[Nicholas Rémillard]] | header6 = | label6 = Location | data6 = [[Miami]], [[Florida]], United States | header7 = | label7 = Topics | data7 = {{plainlist| *[[Economy]] *[[Finance]] *[[Infrastructure]] *[[Art]] & [[Luxury goods|Luxury]] *[[Energy]] *[[Trade]] *[[Agriculture]]}} | header8 = | label8 = Next Event | data8 = April 1–2, 2019 | header9 = | label9 = Sister Organizations | data9 = {{plainlist| *[[Conference of Montreal]] *[[Toronto Global Forum]] *[[Conference of Paris]]}} | header10 = | label10 = Website | data10 = {{URL|http://forum-americas.org/miami}}}}
The '''World Strategic Forum''' is an annual economic event organized by the [[International Economic Forum of the Americas]] since 2011.
==Mission== The World Strategic Forum is a [[not-for-profit organization]] whose mission is to address the major governance challenges and to foster dialogues on national and global issues by bringing together heads of state, the private sector, international organizations and civil society. It also attempts to foster exchanges of information, to promote free discussion on major current economic issues and facilitate meetings between world leaders.<ref>http://forum-americas.org/miami/mission</ref>
The Forum brings together more than 1,400 people from across the globe, every year.<ref>Heroux Pounds, Marcia. "World Leaders head to West Palm Beach". Sun Sentinel [Palm Beach] April 2, 2014 p.1D</ref>
==History== The first Forum was presented in 2011 and was held in [[Palm Beach County Convention Center|Palm Beach, Florida]], until 2014. The subsequent editions, as of 2015, are held in [[Miami]], Florida.<ref>Ostrowski, Jeff. "Strategic Forum ends four-year run in county". The Palm Beach Post [Palm Beach] April 9, 2014 p.B6</ref>
==Notable speakers== See [http://forum-americas.org/miami source] {{columns-list|colwidth=30em| *[[Shaukat Aziz]], [[Prime Minister of Pakistan]] (2004-2007) *[[Willem Buiter]], global chief economist, [[Citi]] *[[Amadou Diallo]], chief executive officer, [[DHL Freight]] *[[Thomas J. Donohue]], president and chief executive officer, [[United States Chamber of Commerce]] (USCC) *Jean-Louis Ekra, chairman and president, [[African Export-Import Bank]] *[[Hage Geingob]], [[Prime Minister of Namibia]] *[[Fred Hochberg]], chairman and president, [[Export-Import Bank of the United States]] (Ex-Im Bank) *Michael Horodniceanu, president, [[MTA Capital Construction]] *[[José Miguel Insulza]], secretary general, [[Organization of American States]] (OAS) *[[Salvador Namburete]], Minister of Energy, [[Mozambique]] *[[Rick Perry]], [[governor]], [[State of Texas]], United States of America *Robert L. Reynolds, president and chief executive officer, [[Putnam Investments]] *[[Rick Scott]], [[governor]], [[State of Florida]], United States of America *[[Strobe Talbott]], president, [[Brookings Institution|Brookings]] *Julio Velarde, governor, [[Central Bank of Peru]] }}
